    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Benson Boone's \"In the Stars\" \r\n\r\nPutting together songs can involve **pattern recognition** - looking for similarities to help solve a problem. For example, you can use patterns to recreate the chorus to \"In the Stars\" using the provided tracks.\r\n\r\nTo complete this level, your code will need:\r\n- Four <code style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 148, 202); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play together</code> blocks\r\n- Each block should contain 4 tracks: Two <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-microphone-stand\" style=\"color: #F99258; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Vocal </span> tracks, a <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-boombox\" style=\"color: #58BEF9; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Bass </span> track, and a <span style=\"padding: 2px; font-size: 12px; color: white; background-color: rgb(76, 86, 97); border: solid 2px #999; border-radius: 5px; margin-right: 2px; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 2.5em;\"> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-guitars\" style=\"color: #64D25A; margin-right: 2px\"></i> Lead </span> track.\r\n- Your song should match the example below!\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/2ffd07a262bb59fa1786b7f8b902e5cb-image-1749246622085.png)",
